That's all the information 
we were able to gather.

00:02:13.980 --> 00:02:14.940
Profile
Yoshikage Kira

00:02:14.530 --> 00:02:19.030
It appears he's done a good job of disposing 
of all evidence of his crimes up to now.

00:02:19.520 --> 00:02:21.230
Yoshikage Kira...

00:02:21.230 --> 00:02:24.120
What do you look like now, 
and what is your name?

00:02:24.670 --> 00:02:26.120
Where are you?

00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:27.990
Summer...

00:02:27.990 --> 00:02:31.960
There are many more tourists around town now.

00:02:32.470 --> 00:02:33.590
Yeah...

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:37.590
I doubt that he'll be able to stay put.

00:02:38.570 --> 00:02:41.890
I'm sure he won't be able 
to resist making a move.

00:02:41.890 --> 00:02:44.350
The summer season is finally upon us.

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:49.240
On July 1st, the beach and rivers in 
Morioh were opened to the public.

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:52.590
There are hordes of tourists 
from the capital and S City,

00:02:52.590 --> 00:02:54.820
making the town even livelier.

00:02:54.820 --> 00:02:58.860
Relaxing at a summer villa, 
camping, fishing, yachting...

00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:03.020
There are many fun activities 
to find here this time of year!

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:06.600
How are you all going 
to enjoy your summer?

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.830
Yes, many fun things...

00:03:09.830 --> 00:03:12.330
I'm sure he has

00:03:12.330 --> 00:03:15.090
many fun things to do, too.

00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:21.740
People live while hiding what's 
deep in their hearts from others.

00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:22.890
But...

00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:24.720
Is there anyone who has

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:28.530
been able to hide their true 
self from others forever?

00:03:31.850 --> 00:03:32.790
Damn it!

00:03:32.790 --> 00:03:36.770
I want to show that woman 
the true Yoshikage Kira.

00:03:37.350 --> 00:03:40.120
I want her to hear how 
I feel deep down inside...

00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:42.630
That I want to take your 
slender neck into these hands

00:03:42.630 --> 00:03:44.870
and strangle you to death.

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:50.080
When my nails are growing, 
I become unable to suppress my urges.

00:03:51.460 --> 00:03:54.770
I just need to be patient until it subsides.

00:03:56.310 --> 00:04:00.430
I'm still not able to perfectly
mimic his handwriting.

00:03:59.420 --> 00:04:01.920
Kosaku Kawajiri

00:04:03.180 --> 00:04:07.300
Kosaku

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:13.610
Josuke Higashikata... Jotaro Kujo...

00:04:13.610 --> 00:04:16.190
It's because of them that I'm in this mess.

00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:22.510
Um...

00:04:22.510 --> 00:04:25.610
Uh... What... are you doing?

00:04:29.370 --> 00:04:32.750
O-Of course. It should be obvious.

00:04:33.260 --> 00:04:35.350
You were reading a book.

00:04:35.350 --> 00:04:37.660
Um, I poured some tea for you.

00:04:37.660 --> 00:04:41.150
I know you probably think that's rare,

00:04:41.150 --> 00:04:43.240
b-but if you'd like some...

00:04:43.690 --> 00:04:46.180
If you don't want it, that's fine, too...

00:05:04.370 --> 00:05:07.220
Oh, look at the time.

00:05:07.220 --> 00:05:09.580
I think I'll go to bed...

00:05:30.740 --> 00:05:33.340
Open up your heart to that woman.

00:05:33.890 --> 00:05:36.100
Show her your true self,

00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:38.060
Yoshikage Kira.

00:05:45.750 --> 00:05:47.450
D-Darling?

00:05:47.760 --> 00:05:50.910
Crap. Opening up is a bad idea.

00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:52.870
They'll find out.

00:05:55.810 --> 00:05:58.620
I'm sorry I startled you.

00:06:00.090 --> 00:06:03.490
H-He was trying to undo 
the buttons in the back?

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.630
"I'm sorry I startled you"?

00:06:06.630 --> 00:06:10.290
Not at all! All of your actions lately

00:06:10.290 --> 00:06:12.490
have been exciting me to no end!

00:06:12.490 --> 00:06:16.960
And they make me feel thrilled! I...

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:18.810
I've fallen

00:06:18.810 --> 00:06:20.680
in love with you.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:31.720
J-Josuke, l-look over there.

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:33.200
What the heck is—

00:06:39.360 --> 00:06:42.560
Is this... Could this be...

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:44.050
T-Terri Funk—

00:06:44.050 --> 00:06:45.280
It's a crop circle!

00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:47.490
Yeah! A crop circle!

00:06:47.490 --> 00:06:49.170
Th-That's amazing!

00:06:49.170 --> 00:06:52.640
I can't believe one of these 
showed up in a field in Morioh!

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:55.430
Something's not right, Okuyasu.

00:06:55.770 --> 00:06:58.550
Take a closer look at the middle of that thing.

00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:06.070
Something's really wrong here!

00:07:07.480 --> 00:07:09.250
You're gonna go in?

00:07:09.250 --> 00:07:11.240
We don't have a choice!

00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:16.800
Be careful.

00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:18.080
Yeah.

00:07:20.790 --> 00:07:22.930
I-Is he alive?

00:07:22.930 --> 00:07:25.900
He's got a scratch on the back of his neck,

00:07:25.900 --> 00:07:27.800
but I think he's just unconscious.

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:30.720
Hey, wake up. Are you all right? Hey!

00:07:30.720 --> 00:07:34.530
I've never seen him at our school.

00:07:35.550 --> 00:07:38.060
Oh, looks like he's awake.

00:07:50.890 --> 00:07:52.290
Where...

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:55.070
Where am I?

00:07:55.070 --> 00:07:56.450
Where?

00:07:56.450 --> 00:07:59.950
You're right in the middle of 
a field in Budogaoka, Morioh.

00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:02.080
Is this Earth?

00:08:03.090 --> 00:08:07.350
Last night, I suddenly felt ill.

00:08:07.350 --> 00:08:10.310
I then lost consciousness, it would seem.

00:08:10.800 --> 00:08:17.080
It's past eight, so I was unconscious 
for thirteen Earth hours.

00:08:22.140 --> 00:08:25.190
He totally tried to pull one over us!

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:29.390
Damn! I can't believe you tried 
to pull such an elaborate prank!

00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:31.790
Man, you sure got me!

00:08:31.790 --> 00:08:34.200
You're a really funny guy!

00:08:34.200 --> 00:08:37.860
So you made a crop circle and waited

00:08:37.860 --> 00:08:40.230
under the grass until someone came by?

00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:42.070
Amazing! That's amazing!

00:08:42.070 --> 00:08:44.460
I can't breathe! My stomach hurts!

00:08:44.980 --> 00:08:45.980
Stomach Medicine

00:08:51.070 --> 00:08:52.260
That's so stupid!

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:55.720
What school do you go to?

00:08:56.260 --> 00:08:57.540
School?

00:08:56.260 --> 00:08:58.850
We love guys like you!

00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:03.950
My planet is in the Magellanic Clouds,
but it has been destroyed.

00:09:04.390 --> 00:09:07.500
I came to Earth to find out

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:11.080
if it's a suitable place to live, 
and if the people are nice.

00:09:12.780 --> 00:09:15.990
That's enough of that. 
If you take the joke too far,

00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:18.740
you're going to ruin your own brilliant idea.

00:09:18.740 --> 00:09:20.370
Here, have a tissue.

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:30.750
Thank you. That was quite delicious.

00:09:32.210 --> 00:09:35.110
W-We should really get to school.

00:09:35.110 --> 00:09:37.180
Y-Yeah, you're right.

00:09:37.180 --> 00:09:38.460
Let's go.

00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:42.840
That guy ate the tissue.

00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:45.140
He's a guy who takes jokes too far.

00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:49.060
The ice cream shop's closed!

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:52.550
And it's our only comfort on Monday mornings...

00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:53.960
It can't be helped.

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:55.720
Let's give up for today.

00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:58.030
Would you like some ice cream?

00:09:58.570 --> 00:10:00.820
Well? Do you want some?

00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:04.560
Yeah, but the shop's closed, 
so there's nothing we can do.

00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:06.330
There's no reason for you to give up.

00:10:06.330 --> 00:10:08.670
I just happen to have two.

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:12.440
We can call it a trade for the tissue earlier.

00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:16.800
Earth seems like a very nice place to live.

00:10:17.340 --> 00:10:18.760
It's cold...

00:10:18.760 --> 00:10:22.220
Wh-Why did you have 
ice cream cones in your bag?

00:10:22.220 --> 00:10:24.690
Are those ice cream cones not good enough?

00:10:24.690 --> 00:10:28.350
That's not what I'm asking! 
Who the hell are you?

00:10:28.350 --> 00:10:31.860
I believe I told you that moments ago...

00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:35.280
Ah! You want to hear me introduce myself?

00:10:35.280 --> 00:10:36.610
It must have slipped my mind.

00:10:37.020 --> 00:10:40.830
My name is Nu Mikitakazo Nshi.

00:10:40.830 --> 00:10:43.280
I am 216 years old.

00:10:43.280 --> 00:10:45.660
My occupation is a spaceship pilot.

00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:47.620
My hobby is having pets.

00:10:48.370 --> 00:10:51.850
I'm even currently carrying 
a house mouse in my bag.

00:10:51.850 --> 00:10:54.380
It is very happy when I pet its back.

00:10:54.380 --> 00:10:57.490
This guy's a Stand user. 
There's no doubt about it.

00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.270
Let's kick his ass, Josuke!

00:10:59.270 --> 00:11:00.940
Calm down, Okuyasu.

00:11:00.940 --> 00:11:02.800
Do you really think a Stand user

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:05.640
would say that he's from 
the Magellanic Clouds?

00:11:05.640 --> 00:11:08.770
Th-Then what the hell is with him?

00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:08.770
There, there, there.

00:11:08.770 --> 00:11:10.680
I have no idea.

00:11:10.680 --> 00:11:12.430
We're gonna have to investigate.

00:11:12.430 --> 00:11:14.370
Don't eat that ice cream.

00:11:14.370 --> 00:11:15.360
Huh?!

00:11:16.850 --> 00:11:19.410
So you're 216, you say?

00:11:19.410 --> 00:11:20.110
Yes.

00:11:20.110 --> 00:11:22.410
Hmm...

00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:22.410
Hmm...

00:11:24.490 --> 00:11:27.740
And your occupation is a spaceship pilot?

00:11:28.670 --> 00:11:31.280
Why do you keep copying me?

00:11:31.280 --> 00:11:32.960
So, what?

00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:38.640
Are you trying to say that you're an alien?

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:42.100
An alien!

00:11:42.100 --> 00:11:43.740
An alien! Yes!

00:11:43.740 --> 00:11:45.990
I should have used that word to begin with.

00:11:45.990 --> 00:11:47.560
I'm an alien.

00:11:47.560 --> 00:11:48.990
Hey, hey, hey, hey...

00:11:48.990 --> 00:11:51.920
Then, like, your... flying saucer?

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:54.270
Could you call over your spaceship?

00:11:54.270 --> 00:11:55.690
You can, right?

00:11:55.690 --> 00:11:56.780
Of course.

00:11:56.780 --> 00:12:01.000
But, sadly, as it is currently on standby 
in space, 1,500,000 kilometers away,

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:02.720
it would take about three days.

00:12:02.720 --> 00:12:03.990
I can't bring it immediately.

00:12:03.990 --> 00:12:06.430
Are you going to call it 
with that watch of yours?

00:12:06.430 --> 00:12:08.660
Oh, how did you know?

00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:11.370
But this is a secret between us.

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:13.620
Please don't tell anyone of this.

00:12:13.620 --> 00:12:16.670
This guy is totally messed up in the head.

00:12:16.670 --> 00:12:18.910
He wasn't joking earlier at all.

00:12:18.910 --> 00:12:20.930
He's a delusional, crazy bastard.

00:12:20.930 --> 00:12:22.360
Should I punch him?

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:24.870
You always want to throw punches first.

00:12:24.870 --> 00:12:27.260
Let's take it a bit further, just to be sure.

00:12:27.260 --> 00:12:30.170
Do you have, like, a ray gun and, like,

00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:32.770
an ultra hyper anti-gravity 
device in your bag?

00:12:32.770 --> 00:12:34.760
Of course I do.

00:12:34.760 --> 00:12:39.530
But I didn't come to Earth to fight, 
so I left them in my spaceship.

00:12:39.530 --> 00:12:44.510
Aw, come on. If you're an 
alien, show us something.

00:12:44.510 --> 00:12:47.980
And your blood wasn't even green.

00:12:47.980 --> 00:12:51.290
Yeah. Alien blood is always green.

00:12:51.830 --> 00:12:54.670
Do you two doubt me?

00:12:54.670 --> 00:12:56.080
Hey, calm down.

00:12:56.080 --> 00:12:58.340
You finally got it? You moron!

00:12:58.340 --> 00:13:00.380
I don't mind going along with pranks,

00:13:00.380 --> 00:13:03.090
but I don't have time to deal 
with delusional freaks like you.

00:13:03.090 --> 00:13:05.150
You didn't have to just come out and say that!

00:13:05.150 --> 00:13:08.100
Shut up! It's better to be up-front!

00:13:10.300 --> 00:13:12.810
What? Is there a fire somewhere?

00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:25.610
Wh-What the hell?

00:13:25.980 --> 00:13:28.300
This sound... I don't like this sound.

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:30.120
This sound...

00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:33.000
Stop this sound!

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:34.730
I don't like this sound!

00:13:34.730 --> 00:13:37.000
I'm allergic to it!

00:13:37.000 --> 00:13:38.340
Make it stop!

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.130
Josuke, this guy's dangerous!

00:13:43.130 --> 00:13:45.770
Let's go. We shouldn't mess with him.

00:13:45.770 --> 00:13:47.380
But don't you think

00:13:47.380 --> 00:13:49.960
leaving him like that is a bit cruel?

00:13:49.960 --> 00:13:52.720
He said he's allergic to that sound, 
right? Just leave him be.

00:13:52.720 --> 00:13:54.710
I'm leaving, Josuke.

00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:56.220
H-Hey!

00:13:56.220 --> 00:13:58.730
Damn it, Okuyasu.

00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:05.360
H-Hey, you okay?

00:14:05.360 --> 00:14:08.110
No... Please,

00:14:08.110 --> 00:14:10.490
take me somewhere I can't hear this sound...

00:14:12.930 --> 00:14:14.660
Wh-What?!

00:14:14.660 --> 00:14:16.460
Please take me away!

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:18.620
A-Are you actually...

00:14:18.620 --> 00:14:23.130
I have a power that allows 
me to turn into anything.

00:14:23.130 --> 00:14:27.260
H-Hurry... I feel like my head 
will split open amidst this sound...

00:14:27.260 --> 00:14:28.310
Please...

00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:32.910
I'll turn into sneakers, so please, 
wear them and take me with you!

00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:36.930
In return, I'll do anything for you!

00:14:38.440 --> 00:14:40.560
Are you a Stand user?!

00:14:44.840 --> 00:14:47.100
Whoa! Y-You're super fast!

00:14:47.100 --> 00:14:49.450
With your powers plus my powers,

00:14:49.450 --> 00:14:52.940
our speed and jumping strength are doubled.

00:14:52.940 --> 00:14:56.060
Are you seriously an alien?!

