00:16:56.470 --> 00:16:58.140
And so...

00:16:58.140 --> 00:17:00.410
Can you turn into this? This thing.

00:17:03.450 --> 00:17:05.310
What is that?

00:17:05.310 --> 00:17:07.370
They're dice!

00:17:07.370 --> 00:17:09.050
I'll make some money using these,

00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:12.380
then I'll split it with you, 
and everyone will be happy!

00:17:12.380 --> 00:17:14.710
What do you do with those?

00:17:14.710 --> 00:17:17.340
Huh? You don't know what dice are?

00:17:17.340 --> 00:17:19.470
I-I'm sorry...

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:21.660
You don't have to apologize.

00:17:21.660 --> 00:17:24.640
It's really easy. I'll show you.

00:17:24.640 --> 00:17:28.750
These are tools that people 
who like games really love.

00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:31.440
They're hard, and they have six sides.

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:36.280
This divot represents the number one, 
and it has them from one through six.

00:17:36.280 --> 00:17:38.470
Ah, yes. I think I'm starting to understand.

00:17:38.470 --> 00:17:41.040
So when there are five divots, 
it's the number five, right?

00:17:41.040 --> 00:17:42.610
Well done, alien!

00:17:42.610 --> 00:17:44.640
And three divots represent a three.

00:17:44.090 --> 00:17:45.660
Yes! Try turning into one.

00:17:45.660 --> 00:17:47.080
Understood.

00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:49.420
That was simple.

00:17:50.190 --> 00:17:53.920
What are you talking about? 
You're way too big.

00:17:53.920 --> 00:17:55.800
You're only supposed to be about this big.

00:17:55.800 --> 00:17:57.590
Also, you've got five on two sides.

00:17:57.590 --> 00:18:00.010
The numbers on a die are from one through six.

00:18:00.010 --> 00:18:03.060
The numbers on one side and its 
opposite side should equal seven.

00:18:03.060 --> 00:18:04.810
Oh, pardon me.

00:18:06.870 --> 00:18:08.460
How about this?

00:18:11.940 --> 00:18:13.400
Th-That tickles!

00:18:13.400 --> 00:18:16.870
Hey, don't laugh. Dice don't talk.

00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:17.810
Huh?

00:18:17.810 --> 00:18:19.150
Come on.

00:18:19.150 --> 00:18:20.530
I-I'll do my best.

00:18:20.530 --> 00:18:23.310
I'm a bit nervous about this, but...

00:18:24.450 --> 00:18:28.330
Yes, you're good! Very good! This is perfect!

00:18:28.330 --> 00:18:30.200
I'm getting excited!

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:34.300
Rohan Kishibe, I hope you have 
some money waiting for me!

00:18:32.200 --> 00:18:34.300
I-I can't breathe...

00:18:35.890 --> 00:18:38.370
Oh, look who it is.

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:41.550
What does Josuke Higashikata want with me?

00:18:41.550 --> 00:18:44.390
This is a rare occurrence.

00:18:44.390 --> 00:18:47.100
Did you get more information concerning Kira?

00:18:47.100 --> 00:18:50.050
No, not exactly...

00:18:50.050 --> 00:18:51.880
Um, well...

00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:54.480
Are you done with work today?

00:18:54.480 --> 00:18:58.090
I was wondering if I could have 
a peek at your next chapter...

00:18:59.260 --> 00:19:01.270
What are you plotting?

00:19:01.270 --> 00:19:02.530
Just spit it out.

00:19:02.530 --> 00:19:05.030
D-Damn...

00:19:05.030 --> 00:19:07.820
I can't hide anything from you, Rohan-sensei.

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:10.670
All right, I'll tell you the truth.

00:19:12.250 --> 00:19:15.850
Please! Play Cee-lo with me!

00:19:15.850 --> 00:19:17.550
Cee-lo?

00:19:17.550 --> 00:19:20.300
To be perfectly honest,

00:19:20.300 --> 00:19:23.320
I have no spending money for the summer.

00:19:23.320 --> 00:19:28.080
Well, I have 30,000 yen. 
It's my life savings.

00:19:28.080 --> 00:19:29.560
But...

00:19:29.560 --> 00:19:33.150
Nowadays, 30,000 yen is gone 
after you make one or two trips

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:35.320
to an amusement park and get some food.

00:19:35.890 --> 00:19:38.570
So all that's left is to make 
more money, or go flat broke.

00:19:38.990 --> 00:19:40.610
Wagering on the thrill!

00:19:40.610 --> 00:19:43.000
Isn't that what youth is all about?

00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:45.740
That's what I think! Don't you agree?!

00:19:48.380 --> 00:19:52.280
Look, I'll be straight with you. 
I've always disliked you.

00:19:52.280 --> 00:19:56.340
So why should I have to play Cee-lo with you?

00:19:56.640 --> 00:19:58.290
Yeah, you're right.

00:19:58.290 --> 00:20:02.560
I'm sure you're not hurting for spending money,

00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:05.220
so you have no reason to play.

00:20:04.060 --> 00:20:05.900
But... All right.

00:20:05.900 --> 00:20:08.170
Huh?! You'll do it?

00:20:08.170 --> 00:20:11.170
I don't dislike games, and this seems fun.

00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:12.810
Come around to the back.

00:20:12.810 --> 00:20:15.600
Thank you, Rohan-sensei.

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:22.700
The shooter rolls 3 dice into the bowl

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:22.700
This will result in paying double

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:22.700
This will result in winning double

00:20:19.360 --> 00:20:22.700
The larger number wins (here, the 6)

00:20:19.580 --> 00:20:21.370
Do these rules work for you?

00:20:21.370 --> 00:20:22.700
No arguments here.

00:20:22.700 --> 00:20:24.520
Chips cost 1,000 yen each.

00:20:24.520 --> 00:20:26.420
And when you roll the 
three dice into the bowl,

00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:28.860
if even one spills out, 
you lose then and there.

00:20:28.860 --> 00:20:29.950
Got it.

00:20:29.950 --> 00:20:33.460
All right. Let's tape the rules up here.

00:20:33.460 --> 00:20:35.050
Okay, let's do this!

00:20:35.050 --> 00:20:36.340
Wait.

00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:38.520
We won't be using your dice.

00:20:38.520 --> 00:20:39.340
Huh?!

00:20:39.340 --> 00:20:42.630
We'll be playing with these 
dice I had in the house.

00:20:44.120 --> 00:20:48.970
U-Um, is there something wrong with my dice?

00:20:48.970 --> 00:20:52.580
No idea. There's just something 
that I don't like about them.

00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:53.750
And...

00:20:53.750 --> 00:20:57.980
I did say this seemed fun, 
but I wasn't talking about Cee-lo.

00:20:57.980 --> 00:21:02.860
I meant that it'd be fun taking 
your 30,000 yen from you.

00:21:03.900 --> 00:21:07.000
When you lose, you'd better pay up for real.

00:21:07.000 --> 00:21:09.790
It doesn't matter how well
acquainted we are, Josuke-kun.

00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:19.540
Yes! Those dice are the ones 
that the alien turned into!

00:21:19.540 --> 00:21:23.350
I snuck them into your house ahead of time!

00:21:23.350 --> 00:21:25.470
I'm such a villain.

00:21:25.470 --> 00:21:30.530
It won't be much, but I'll be making 
some money off of you, Rohan-sensei.

00:21:30.530 --> 00:21:33.100
Now, let's roll to see who goes first.

00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:35.690
I rolled a four.

00:21:37.410 --> 00:21:38.360
Yes!

00:21:38.360 --> 00:21:41.350
All right, you go first. Go ahead and roll.

00:21:41.350 --> 00:21:42.180
Ow!

00:21:42.180 --> 00:21:42.740
O...

00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:46.570
O-Ow! I accidentally hit the table.

00:21:50.060 --> 00:21:51.830
Hurry up and bet and roll your dice.

00:21:51.830 --> 00:21:53.060
R-Right...

00:21:53.060 --> 00:21:58.580
I-I'll start off with two, I think, 
so that'll be 2,000 yen.

00:21:58.580 --> 00:22:00.340
Okay, here's two.

00:22:00.340 --> 00:22:03.690
If I roll a one, a two, and a three,
I'll have to pay double,

00:22:03.690 --> 00:22:07.090
so I really need to make sure 
I don't get one, two, and three.

00:22:07.090 --> 00:22:11.310
Better not get a one, two, and three! 
Not a one, two, and three!

00:22:13.310 --> 00:22:15.620
I-I'll go really lightly on the first roll.

00:22:15.620 --> 00:22:17.560
Just to test the waters...

00:22:17.560 --> 00:22:19.810
Here we go... Lightly.

00:22:21.090 --> 00:22:22.510
How's that?!

00:22:24.070 --> 00:22:24.660
Huh?!

00:22:24.660 --> 00:22:25.190
What?

00:22:25.190 --> 00:22:27.560
A-An omen...

00:22:27.560 --> 00:22:28.680
What?

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:31.250
Triple sixes, AKA "omen."

00:22:31.250 --> 00:22:34.450
Josuke wins five times what 
he wagered from Rohan.

00:22:34.450 --> 00:22:37.380
S-Stupid! You're not supposed 
to start off with that!

00:22:37.380 --> 00:22:39.340
E-Er, I mean...

00:22:39.340 --> 00:22:41.710
I meant that was some stupid luck!

00:22:41.710 --> 00:22:44.550
A triple six, meaning you have 
to pay five times my bet...

00:22:44.550 --> 00:22:47.070
It almost seems like I'm cheating!

00:22:51.040 --> 00:22:54.710
Hmph. It seems you've already earned 
10,000 yen in spending money.

00:22:54.710 --> 00:22:56.530
Let's continue the game.

00:22:54.710 --> 00:22:59.160
I can't believe my luck myself...

00:22:57.260 --> 00:22:59.160
It's my turn next.

00:22:59.160 --> 00:23:02.270
I want to get back what I just lost, so I'm...

00:23:02.930 --> 00:23:04.780
going with ten.

00:23:04.780 --> 00:23:06.280
Ten?

00:23:06.280 --> 00:23:07.530
All right! Go!

00:23:11.810 --> 00:23:14.280
One, two, and three. The wager is doubled!

00:23:13.660 --> 00:23:17.160
The shooter rolls 3 dice into the bowl

00:23:13.660 --> 00:23:17.160
This will result in paying double

00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:17.160
Rohan has to pay Josuke double what he wagered.

00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:21.050
This is too much! This is way too much!

00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:24.720
Does that alien not know 
what "holding back" means?

00:23:28.010 --> 00:23:32.340
Crap... He's totally suspicious of me!

